<!-- Node: "DOOM 3 spec requirements" -->
<div class="body_box_header">DOOM 3 spec requirements</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2157" title="View user profile.">method</a> on Tuesday, July 20, 2004 - 21:27</small><br /><br />
Todd Hollenshead, Id Software CEO, said that DOOM 3 will require:<br />
<i><br />
A 1.5-gigahertz Intel Pentium 4 chip or AMD Athlon 1500.<br />
384 megabytes of memory.<br />
Two gigabytes of hard drive space.<br />
An nVidia GeForce 3 graphics card or better; or an ATI Technologies 8500 or better.</i><br />
<br />
If your pc doesn't meet the spec requirements head over to <a href = "http://www.chron.com/cs/CDA/ssistory.mpl/tech/weekly/2690450">Houston Chronicle</a> to read on how you can improve your pc.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/login" >Login</a> or <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/register" >Register</a> to post comments
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Update Finished" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Update Finished</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/8" title="View user profile.">Jherax</a> on Saturday, July 17, 2004 - 22:15</small><br /><br />
Applied a few updates tonight, the biggest of which includes major changes to the layout when you are logged in under your user account.<br />
<br />
Logged in users now have the benefit of having only 1 ad appear on screen, as well as a new, modified interface. Since browsing the site with only a single ad is infinitely faster than trying trying to surf with all three of them visible at once, I highly recommend logging in or creating a new user if you haven't yet.<br />
<br />
Oh, and don't forget to leave comments and feedback, we like that kind of stuff around here :)
<br /><br />
<a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/420#comment" title="Jump to the first comment of this posting.">4 comments</a>
