<!-- Node: "Contributing Content" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Contributing Content</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/8" title="View user profile.">Jherax</a> on Saturday, July 17, 2004 - 21:43</small><br /><br />
So, you want to help contribute editing-related content to RUST | Gamedesign.net... great! Here are a few guidelines for content submission if you are interesting in writing an article or two to be added to our editing handbooks.

<!-- break -->

<blockquote>
1. <b>Check it once, then check it again!</b><p>
Be sure to double check your article or tutorial for spelling and accuracy errors! Nothing's more disappointing then getting halfway through a great tutorial and releasing that you can't go from one stage to the next because the author forget a step.</p>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
<p>2. <b>Stay focused!</b><p>
Make sure your article/tutorial stays focused on your topic. Although it may seem great to announce to the world about your new pet dog, Fido, somewhere in that article of yours, don't forget that someone looking to learn three point lighting techniques probably won't care whether you named the dog Fido, Pluto, or Dips--t for that matter.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/login" >Login</a> or <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/register" >Register</a> to post comments &middot; <a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/419" title="Read the rest of this posting." class="read-more"><b>Read more</b></a>
</div><br />


